<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>How does an increase in the natural rate of unemployment affect the Phillips Curve?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Shifts both short-run and long-run curves right</option>
            <option letter="b">Only shifts the long-run curve right</option>
            <option letter="c">Only affects the slope of the curves</option>
            <option letter="d">Has no effect on either curve</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>When the natural rate of unemployment increases, both the long-run Phillips Curve (which is vertical at the natural rate) and the short-run Phillips Curve shift to the right. This shows that all inflation rates are now associated with higher unemployment levels.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
